<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,307,850,876]" box="[189,307,850,876]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,307,850,876]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,307,850,876]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[186,1400,896,1169]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
A species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" box="[340,453,896,922]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[340,453,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Stygiiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[461,565,897,923]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with normal mouthparts. Distinguishable from congeners by its smaller body (L = 
<quantity box="[314,441,932,958]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="10.0">10–16 mm</quantity>
) and shorter legs in relation to H, by the ozopores being placed on or right behind the pro-metazonal suture instead of at considerable distance behind it, and in several aspects of gonopod structures (
<figureCitation box="[313,415,1002,1028]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[197,1384,282,1779]" captionTargetId="figure-12@26.[189,1398,263,1787]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 10. Left gonopods of species of Stygiiulus stat. nov., mesal views. A. S. ausugi (Manfredi, 1953) comb.nov.,topotype♂(NHMD).B.S.illyricus(Verhoeff,1929)comb.nov.,redrawnfromVerhoeff (1929). C. S. insularis (Strasser, 1938) comb. nov., redrawn from Antić et al. (2018). D. S. maximus (Verhoeff, 1929) comb. nov., redrawn from Verhoeff (1930). E. S. seewaldi (Strasser, 1967) comb. nov., redrawn and modified from Strasser (1967). F. S. tobias (Berlese, 1886) comb. nov., ♂ from Grotta [Cave] del Subiolo (NHMD). Abbreviations: do = distal outgrowth of velum. Drawn not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6323028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6323028/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Fig.10C</figureCitation>
), viz., ridge- rather than knob-like internal lobe of the promere, spoon-shaped mesomere, rather robust opisthomere without a posterior hump (the latter shared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" box="[1051,1188,1037,1064]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seewaldii" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1051,1188,1037,1064]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">S. seewaldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1196,1327,1037,1064]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), long basal spine at flagellum channel (sometimes present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[825,978,1072,1099]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundatus" status="comb. et stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[825,978,1072,1099]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">S. rotundatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[986,1196,1072,1099]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">comb. et stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[1253,1399,1072,1099]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriatus" status="comb. et stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1253,1399,1072,1099]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">S. fimbriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,400,1108,1134]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">comb. et stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and the presence of a distinct distal outgrowth (do) on velum (seen also in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[1269,1399,1108,1134]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seewaldi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1269,1399,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">S. seewaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,316,1143,1169]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[371,469,1143,1169]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tobias" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[371,469,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">S. tobias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[476,607,1143,1169]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,399,1208,1234]" box="[189,399,1208,1234]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,399,1208,1234]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,399,1208,1234]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Descriptive notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[187,1399,1255,1352]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">ANTENNAE. 1.6 times as long as head and 1.65 as long as H in the male, and 1.35 and 1.3 times, respectively, in the female; antennomere 5 ca 1.6 as long as broad; antennomeres 2 and 5 subequal in length, ca 1.3 times as long as 3 and 4, and 1.5 times as long as 6.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,1391,1453]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">TARSUS OF MID- BODY LEGS. Ca 2.7 times as long as tibia and ca 3.7 times as long as apical claw. Mid-body legs 1.25 times as long as H in the the male and 0.7 times in the female.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[188,1399,1491,1765]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
FEMALE SEXUAL CHARACTERS. Leg-pairs 1 and 2 visibly longer and thicker than following legs. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[198,306,1526,1553]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,231,1681,1707]" captionTargetBox="[345,1243,265,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[325,1262,262,1645]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 11. Left vulvae of species of Stygiiulus stat. nov. (A–D) and representatives of (other) Julini/ Leptoiulini (E) and Typhloiulini/blind Julini/Leptoiulini in caudal, somewhat mesal views. A. S. ausugi (Manfredi, 1953) comb. nov., ♀ from Grotta [Cave] del Calgeron (NHMD). B. S. illyricus (Verhoef, 1929) comb. nov., ♀ from Rabakova Cave (IZB). C. S. insularis (Strasser, 1938) comb. nov., topotype ♀ (CBSS). D. S. tobias (Berlese, 1886) comb. nov., ♀ from Grotta [Cave] del Subiolo (NHMD). E. Leptoiulus cf. trilineatus(C.L. Koch, 1847), ♀ from Belasitsa Mtn, Bulgaria. F. Serboiulus spelaeophilus Gulička, 1967, ♀ from Vodni Pech Cave (NMNHS). G. Typhloiulus (Inversotyphlus) lobifer Attems, 1951, ♀ from Minjera-Bauxite Mine (IBER). H. Typhloiulus (s. str.) strictus (Latzel, 1882), ♀ from Kunino (IBER). Abbreviations: at = anterior tube; la = lateral ampulla; lt = lateral tube; ma = median ampulla; mt = median tube; op = operculum; pa = posterior ampulla; pt = posterior tube. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6323030" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6323030/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
) of nearly equal width in both the sagittal and the transverse planes, mostly symmetric; bursa with a narrow median cleft; each valve distally with a vertical row of 2–4 setae; operculum (op) proximally broad, distally abruptly narrowing, ending with a more or less straight apical margin, exceeding bursa by ca 
<superScript attach="right" box="[453,462,1632,1646]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">1</superScript>
⁄ 
<subScript attach="left" box="[467,476,1642,1656]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">8</subScript>
of total height of vulva, disto-laterally with one vertical row of setae each side. Receptaculum seminis consisting of a very short and narrow, somewhat bent, median tube (mt) leading to a minute piriform ampulla (ma), and a slightly longer, mostly straight, lateral tube (lt) ending in a minute spherical ampulla (la).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1381,1803,1878]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,339,1803,1829]" box="[189,339,1803,1829]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,339,1803,1829]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,339,1803,1829]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1381,1850,1878]" box="[189,1381,1850,1878]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
Known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[436,486,1850,1876]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
locality, the Čampari Pit on the island of Cres in 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1135,1850,1876]" name="Croatia" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1150,1234,1850,1876]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1998,2024]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1099,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-332@33.[189,1398,1099,1960]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 13. General distribution of the species of the genus Stygiiulus stat. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6323034" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6323034/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
, red square).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,301,1915,1941]" box="[189,301,1915,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,301,1915,1941]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,301,1915,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[187,1399,1962,2023]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">
<bibRefCitation author="Strasser K." box="[189,379,1962,1988]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" pagination="389 - 407" refId="ref22248" refString="Strasser K. 1938. Neue Diplopoden der Insel Cherso. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere 71 (4 - 6): 389 - 407." type="journal article" year="1938">Strasser’s (1938)</bibRefCitation>
description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[541,669,1962,1988]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Typhloiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[541,669,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">S. insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[673,797,1962,1988]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was based upon 
<specimenCount box="[982,1124,1962,1988]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" type="female">four females</specimenCount>
only. Due to the absence of male specimens, this species has remained enigmatic for 80 years, until 
<bibRefCitation author="Antic D. Z. &amp; Drazina T. &amp; Rada T. &amp; Lucic L. &amp; Makarov S. E." box="[1032,1242,1997,2023]" pageId="17" pageNumber="47" pagination="258 - 294" refId="ref20375" refString="Antic D. Z., Drazina T., Rada T., Lucic L. R &amp; Makarov S. E. 2018. Review of the genus Typhloiulus Latzel, 1884 in the Dinaric region, with a description of four new species and the first description of the male of Typhloiulus insularis Strasser, 1938 (Diplopoda: Julida: Julidae). Zootaxa 4455 (2): 258 - 294. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4455.2.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Antić 
<emphasis box="[1102,1159,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
described the
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[187,1399,265,679]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">
first male and, according to the gonopod structure, hypothesized this species could belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" box="[1286,1398,265,291]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1286,1398,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">Stygiiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,291,301,327]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Here we follow that assumption, which is further supported by the vulval structure, and formally transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[284,383,335,361]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Typhloiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis box="[284,383,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" box="[542,654,335,361]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[542,654,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">Stygiiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[661,765,336,362]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, this species is obviously different externally compared to other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" box="[397,509,370,396]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[397,509,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">Stygiiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,616,371,397]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
members, and is characterized by a smaller body and proportionatelly shorter antennae, as well as by a more anterior position of the ozopores.And while these external differences (or some of them) may be connected with its currently unknown ecology rather than with its phylogenetic affinities, certain gonopod characters, viz., the aforementioned spoon-like shape of the mesomere and the robustness of the opisthomere, plus a ridge- rather than knob-like internal lobe of the promere leave some doubts about the exact systematic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[704,803,546,572]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Typhloiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis box="[704,803,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But since the general gonopod conformation in this species is much more similar to other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" box="[609,721,582,608]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Stygiiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[609,721,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">Stygiiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[727,828,582,608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
than to any other typhloiulinine/blind leptoiulinine genus, we have opted here to formally place this interesting taxon in the aforementioned genus. Nevertheless, we are aware that in the future this tiny species could find its place in another (new) genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,1398,718,815]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">
The Čampari Pit is also the 
<typeStatus box="[520,569,718,744]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
locality of another julid species, the pachyiulinine 
<taxonomicName authority="Strasser, 1938" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1938" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Chersoiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciliatus">
<emphasis box="[1168,1398,718,744]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">Chersoiulus ciliatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Strasser K." box="[189,353,753,779]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" pagination="389 - 407" refId="ref22248" refString="Strasser K. 1938. Neue Diplopoden der Insel Cherso. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere 71 (4 - 6): 389 - 407." type="journal article" year="1938">Strasser, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vagalinski &amp; Borissov &amp; Bobeva &amp; Canciani &amp; Antić" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[429,556,753,779]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Typhloiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[429,556,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">S. insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[564,691,753,779]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1938" box="[748,866,753,779]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Chersoiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciliatus">
<emphasis box="[748,866,753,779]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">C. ciliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are strict endemics of this pit and are listed as critically endangered species (CR) in the Red Book of the Croatian cave dwelling fauna (
<bibRefCitation author="Ozimec R. &amp; Bedek J. &amp; Gottstein S. &amp; Jalzic B. &amp; Slapnik R. &amp; Stamol V. &amp; Bilandzija H. &amp; Drazina T. &amp; Kletecki E. &amp; Komericki A. &amp; Lukic M. &amp; Pavlek M." box="[1172,1382,788,814]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" refId="ref21849" refString="Ozimec R., Bedek J., Gottstein S., Jalzic B., Slapnik R., Stamol V., Bilandzija H., Drazina T., Kletecki E., Komericki A., Lukic M. &amp; Pavlek M. 2009. Crvena knjiga spiljske faune Hrvatske. [Red book of Croatian cave dwelling fauna]. In: Ozimec R. &amp; Katusic L. (eds) Ministarstvo kulture. Drzavni zavod za zastitu prirode, Zagreb." type="book" year="2009">
Ozimec 
<emphasis box="[1266,1320,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
